■ Information on app access permission consent regulations

In accordance with the provisions of Article 22-2 (Consent to Access Rights) of the Information and Communications Network Act, matters necessary for service use are divided into essential/optional rights, and the contents are as follows.

[Required access rights]
- The app does not have the required access rights.

[Optional access rights]
- Camera: You can attach photos or use the code and image search functions.
- Save: You can upload files saved on the device to the app, or download files provided by the app to the device.
- Microphone: Used when using AR products.

※ You can use the service even if you do not agree to the optional access rights.
